TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$a=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);
$b=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);
$c=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);

BEGIN_TEXT

$PAR

Let \( h(x) = \begin{cases}
      x & \textrm{if } x < 0 \\
    x^2 & \textrm{if } 0 < x \leq 2 \\
    8-x & \textrm{if } x > 2 \\
\end{cases}
\)

$PAR
Find each of the following limits. If the limit does not exist, enter "n" below. $PAR

(a) \(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 0^+} h(x)\) $BR
(b) \(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 0} h(x)\) $BR
(c) \(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 1} h(x)\) $BR
(d) \(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 2^-} h(x)\) $BR
(e) \(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 2^+} h(x)\) $BR
(f) \(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 2} h(x)\) 

$PAR

(a) \{ans_rule(10)\} $BR
(b) \{ans_rule(10)\} $BR
(c) \{ans_rule(10)\} $BR
(d) \{ans_rule(10)\} $BR
(e) \{ans_rule(10)\} $BR
(f) \{ans_rule(10)\}

END_TEXT

ANS(fun_cmp("0", var=>"n"));
ANS(fun_cmp("0", var=>"n"));
ANS(fun_cmp("1", var=>"n"));
ANS(fun_cmp("4", var=>"n"));
ANS(fun_cmp("6", var=>"n"));
ANS(fun_cmp("n", var=>"n"));

